name: Dolphin
description: Dolphins are highly intelligent marine mammals known for their playful behavior.

name: Blue Whale
description: The blue whale is the largest animal known to have ever existed.

name: Sea Turtle
description: Sea turtles are marine reptiles with a history dating back to the time of the dinosaurs.

name: Jellyfish
description: Jellyfish are free-swimming marine animals with umbrella-shaped bells and tentacles.

name: Octopus
description: Octopuses are known for their intelligence, ability to camouflage, and unique appearance.

name: Seahorse
description: Seahorses are small marine fish known for their horse-like head and prehensile tail.

name: Starfish
description: Starfish, or sea stars, are echinoderms with typically five arms extending from a central disc.

name: Penguin
description: Penguins are flightless birds that live in the Southern Hemisphere, especially in Antarctica.

name: Sea Lion
description: Sea lions are marine mammals characterized by external ear flaps and long foreflippers.
